<p>
The green signifies when I went for vacation, and the red signifies when currently people are partying.
</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>No one is safe until everyone is safe.</p>
</blockquote>

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>
Is it then really worth the risk? When majority is not vaccinated, and the current vaccinations (full two doses) might not be enough to keep variants at bay. 
Is the burger or pub alcohol really worth putting ourselves to risk? Is the family gathering so important when it has not been long that we suffered through the consequences of our lapses in judgement. Are we really this incapable of finding inner happiness, with so much luxuries that have been showered upon our lives? Is meeting people (as many) with masks and social distancing without social food consumption so so important that we might have to see the mass graves and black body bags again?
</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->
